In a project you implement a piece
in the first exam you are implementing that again from scratch by yourself. no ai, chatgpt, online, anything. should be the same thing as phase zero? but we are not sure. some people need to retake it but the pass rate is very high. you can take that exam up to three times. you take this exam online/proctored.

Do phase 0 assignment. practice a couple times. really get familiar with it. THere is a time limit on exam. 4 hour time limit. 3 and a half hours to do it, half an hour to turn it in. That is usually a lot more time than many people need. but if you find that things arent working, and time limit is crushing you, talk to the professor and he will help you. 

We are teaching ourselves java. He is not gonna drag us through. we are going to read a book that they provide, we will read certain portions of that book and learn java. if you don't like that book, find online resources. 

